Health care stocks advanced late Friday afternoon with the NYSE Health Care Index up 0.3% and the Health Care Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLV) adding 0.2%. 

The iShares Biotechnology ETF (IBB) rose 0.9%. 

In sector news, the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention plans to conduct a large study into the potential relationship between vaccines and autism, Reuters reported. 

In corporate news, Oruka Therapeutics ORKA shares rose 4.3% after the company said preclinical data on its monoclonal antibody ORKA-002 support potential extended dosing intervals and show equivalent potency to bimekizumab in plaque psoriasis. 

Walgreens Boots Alliance WBA jumped 7.4% after the drugstore chain agreed to be acquired by an affiliate of Sycamore Partners in a deal worth up to $23.7 billion. 

Molina Healthcare MOH and Molina Healthcare of Texas agreed to a $40 million settlement with Texas following a Medicaid fraud investigation. Molina shares rose 1.4%. 

Vertex Pharmaceuticals VRTX said Thursday that its Journavx non-opioid pain killer was added by UnitedHealth Group's (UNH) drug plan unit Optum Rx to its formulary. Vertex shares increased 0.7%.

